The paper deals with the problem of mesh labeling, which is a common task in computer vision and graphics. The proposed method uses a data-driven approach to improve the labeling accuracy, without requiring any prior knowledge about the scene or the relationship among classes. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, such as computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, cs.CV and cs.GR are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the problem of mesh labeling and are commonly used in related research.
